      <h1 class='title'>Variation of instalments or remission of lump sum</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c309GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_309gc' title='Col. 309GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c309GC' name='column_309gc' href='#column_309gc' rel='bookmark'>309GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03965'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_576' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        41 (1) If in the exercise of its powers under Article 97 of the 1981 Order the court orders that a lump sum required to be paid under this Schedule is to be paid by instalments, the court, on an application made by either the person liable to pay or the person entitled to receive that sum, may vary that order by varying&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) the number of instalments payable,</li>
        <li>(b) the amount of any instalment payable, and</li>
        <li>(c) the date on which any instalment becomes payable.</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03966'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_577' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) On the hearing of a complaint for the enforcement, revocation, suspension or variation of an order under this Schedule which provides for the payment of a lump sum the court may remit the whole or any part of that sum.
      </p>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
      </ol>
      
